                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Only applicable with 2-position manual bypass switch(es)</p>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row class="- topic/row ">
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Output couple switch</p>
                        </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">
                              <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For normally closed (NC): </b>Closed</p>
                           <p class="- topic/p ">
                              <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For normally open
(NO): </b>Open</p>
                        </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">If applicable</p>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row class="- topic/row ">
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Output breaker(s)</p>
                        </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Open</p>
                        </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Consumers must be volt free</p>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                     <row class="- topic/row ">
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Outgoing feeders</p>
                        </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">Open</p>
                        </entry>
                        <entry class="- topic/entry ">
                           <p class="- topic/p ">If applicable,
consumers must be volt free</p>
                        </entry>
                     </row>
                  </tbody>
               </tgroup>
            </table>
         </section>
      </conbodydiv>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">How to Perform a Black Start</title>
         <p class="- topic/p ">This procedure
is for one unit. For a system with multiple units, repeat the procedure for the other units.</p>
         <note type="important" class="- topic/note ">The DC capacitors must be charged before connecting the load to the batteries.</note>
         <note class="- topic/note ">Read the complete procedure before performing the procedure.</note>
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Charge the DC capacitors:</p>
               <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Keep the charging/discharging switch in position 2 (charge)
until the warning LED turns off.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for black start on the inverter input
switch: </b>With the charging/discharging switch still in position
2 (charge), close the inverter input switch. If not possible, release
the charging/discharging switch and quickly close the inverter input
switch.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <b platform="PxW" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Only for black start on the battery breaker: </b>With the charging/discharging switch still in position 2 (charge),
close the battery breaker. If not possible, release the charging/discharging
switch and quickly close the battery breaker.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Release the charging/discharging switch.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">After about 10 seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> shows <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Standby</codeph>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Lamp test button</b> and check that all operating
status and alarm LEDâ€™s are illuminated.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">ON button</b> for one second on the front panel
to turn on the system. After a few seconds the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Display</b> will
show <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph ">Batt. operation time &gt; ...min.</codeph>.</p>
               <note class="- topic/note ">The
time will only be shown if an advanced battery monitor is installed.</note>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Press the<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Number 9 key</b> to check that the system output
voltage is within the tolerance range.</p>
               <draft-comment translate="no" class="- topic/draft-comment ">NEED TO CHECK
IF THIS IS CORRECT. For SDC should itbe nr. 8? also bit incorrect
to say system for SDC since here we do not have a system component
doing anything active?</draft-comment>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check on the mimic diagram that the green inverter
LED and the green static switch EN LED is illuminated.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Check on the mimic diagram that the green output
voltage LED is illuminated.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Close the output breaker.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Close any outgoing feeders.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">The system will now supply the load until the batteries are
discharged.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">When the rectifier mains and/or bypass mains
are available again close the respective mains breaker.</p>
            </li>
            <li platform="SDC" class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">When the rectifier mains is available again
close the rectifier mains breaker.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Confirm any alarms by pressing the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">C key</b> twice.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">Make sure the system operates correctly and no alarms are present.</p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </section>
